{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:07:27.483126+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9c34a6ceca64494a1fd10d7b2c1290f7e62e2930)", "id": "lc_6fedb719-bdc1-4778-87cc-da84696b6cf3"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper CLI.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom . import profiles, runner\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"vidpack\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"vidpack 0.1.0\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"profile\", help=\"Profile name defined in profiles.toml\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"input\", help=\"Path to input media file\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"-o\", \"--output\", help=\"Output path (default: derived from input + profile container)\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Print the ffmpeg command without running it\")\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    args = build_parser().parse_args(argv)\n    profile = profiles.load_profile(args.profile)\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    output_path = Path(args.output) if args.output else input_path.with_suffix(f\".{profile['container']}\")\n\n    if output_path.exists() and not args.dry_run:\n        print(f\"error: output {output_path} already exists; refusing to overwrite\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 2\n\n    cmd = runner.build_ffmpeg_command(profile, input_path, output_path)\n    if args.dry_run:\n        print(\" \".join(cmd))\n        return 0\n    return runner.run(cmd)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_64f9a5c6-f7a9-4f12-9916-fe50e1deb6cc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b05d6469-7937-4e07-be91-dc577df99b14", "tool_call_id": "call_58064daee6d0492dbcdba28c", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:07:27.615062+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_83463f0a-1d72-4805-830e-1a4aff3d8aa5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n    cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n\n    container = profile[\"container\"]\n    if container == \"gif\":\n        # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n        fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n        cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n    else:\n        video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n        audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n        cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n        if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n        if \"crf\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n        if scale and scale != \"source\":\n            cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n\n    cmd.append(str(output_path))\n    return cmd\n\n\ndef run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n    return subprocess.call(cmd)\n", "id": "lc_06d23b4d-03ad-412a-a0f3-f67cf39ef60d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c382475a-2ec4-4554-89cd-73ed15444558", "tool_call_id": "call_63462f07bfd8448f820e05dc", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:10:56.687397+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have a clear picture. Let me summarize my findings:\n\n**Issue #1** by BruceKZ reports that `vidpack gif` produces washed-out, banded GIF output compared to a two-pass ffmpeg palettegen/paletteuse pipeline or gifski.\n\n**Code analysis confirms the issue is valid:**\n- In `runner.py` (line ~15-17), the GIF branch only applies `fps` and `scale` filters — there is **no palette generation at all**, not even single-pass. The code runs: `ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos output.gif`\n- A proper high-quality GIF pipeline requires two passes: (1) generate an optimized 256-color palette with `palettegen`, then (2) apply it with `paletteuse`. Without this, ffmpeg's default dithering produces the banding the reporter describes.\n- The `profiles.toml` comment acknowledges this is a known limitation tracked in the issue tracker.\n\nThis is a **confirmed, valid bug/enhancement request** — the issue accurately describes real behavior that matches the code. Let me add a label and a triage comment.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 745, "prompt_tokens": 8666, "total_tokens": 9411, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 420, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8640, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000690564, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 4.2414e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00064815}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963830-ZmBHrGsXBcG0EG7Db8wu", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b4-a07f-7d83-ab72-1c85d36d32f9-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "issue_write", "args": {"method": "update", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01", "issue_number": 1, "labels": ["bug", "enhancement"]}, "id": "call_d10c6aed13d7447a8c9890fe", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8666, "output_tokens": 745, "total_tokens": 9411, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8640}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 420}}}}]}}}
