{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:11:16.901929+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Label write failed due to token permissions. Let me add a comment instead.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 529, "prompt_tokens": 9048, "total_tokens": 9577, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 19, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8640, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000668814, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000208584, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00046023}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963857-KuWv0LUpARFktNZB1lWM", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b7-d3d5-7c81-971b-bbd609c68b92-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"body": "## Triage — confirmed valid\n\nThank you for the clear report, @BruceKZ. I've reviewed the code and can confirm this is a real issue, not just perception.\n\n### Root cause\n\nIn `src/vidpack/runner.py`, the GIF branch only applies an fps + scale filter:\n\n```\nffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos\" output.gif\n```\n\nThere is **no palette generation or paletteuse filter** at all. This means ffmpeg uses its default (naïve) color quantization per frame, which produces the banding and color wash-out you described.\n\n### Why two-pass is the standard\n\nThe correct approach for high-quality GIF output from ffmpeg is:\n\n1. **Pass 1 — palettegen:** `ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,palettegen\" palette.png`\n2. **Pass 2 — paletteuse:** `ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -i palette.png -lavfi \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos [x]; [x][1:v] paletteuse=dither=bayer:bayer_scale=5\" output.gif`\n\nThis is also acknowledged in the `profiles.toml` comment.\n\n### Suggested fix\n\nUpdate `build_ffmpeg_command()` in `runner.py` to:\n- Run a subprocess to generate a palette file (pass 1) using a temp file.\n- Then pass that palette to the main ffmpeg call with `paletteuse` (pass 2).\n\nAlternatively, as a quicker improvement, a single-pass approach using `split[s0][s1];[s0]palettegen[p];[s1][p]paletteuse` in a complex filtergraph would improve quality without a second subprocess.\n\n### Labels\n\nI was unable to apply labels (`bug`, `enhancement`) due to token permissions, but both would be appropriate here — it's a **bug** in output quality and an **enhancement** to the GIF pipeline.", "issue_number": 1, "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01"}, "id": "call_549bfd99ccf8427faf805c5b", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9048, "output_tokens": 529, "total_tokens": 9577, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8640}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 19}}}}]}}}
